external_knowledge:
- Date refers to the date the data was recorded; 
- Cumulative total refers to the total number of tests performed; 
- New cases refer to the number of new cases reported; 
- New deaths refer to the number of new deaths reported; 
- Cumulative cases and deaths refer to the total number of cases and deaths reported, respectively; 
- Source information includes the URL, label, and publication date of the data source; 
- Notes refer to additional comments or information related to the data entry; 
- The data is ordered by country name and then by date, with the latest dates appearing first.

sql:
SELECT MAX(date) AS most_recent_date
FROM data_entries
WHERE country_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The date range of '2021-01-01' to '2021-12-31' implies a yearly aggregation; 
- The country in question is the United States; 
- The terms 'tests performed', 'new cases', and 'total deaths' refer to COVID-19 metrics.
